arguments: {"context": {"sessionId": "session_1731645100000_v3w4x5y6z", "workspaceId": "ws_blockchain", "sessionDescription": "Adding gas tips", "sessionMemory": "Documenting best practices", "toolContext": "Appending section", "primaryGoal": "Document optimization", "subgoal": "Add tips"}, "filepath": "/docs/development-guide.md", "content": "
## Gas Optimization Tips

### Storage vs Memory
- Use `memory` for temporary data
- Use `storage` only when necessary
- Cache storage variables in memory

### Loop Optimization
- Cache array length outside loops
- Use `++i` instead of `i++`
- Avoid expensive operations in loops

### Data Types
- Use `uint256` over smaller uints (cheaper)
- Pack variables to save storage slots
- Use `bytes32` instead of `string` when possible

### Functions
- Mark view/pure functions correctly
- Use external over public when possible
- Batch operations to save gas

### Examples
```solidity
// Bad
for (uint i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
    // expensive operation
}

// Good
uint256 len = array.length;
for (uint256 i; i < len; ++i) {
    // expensive operation
}
```
"}

