arguments: {"context": {"sessionId": "session_1731758700000_d5e6f7g8h", "workspaceId": "ws_1731758700000_i9j0k1l2m", "sessionDescription": "Creating WebSocket guide", "sessionMemory": "Real-time features documentation", "toolContext": "Integration guide", "primaryGoal": "Document WebSocket usage", "subgoal": "Create WebSocket guide"}, "filePath": "/docs/integrations/websockets.md", "content": "# WebSocket Integration Guide

## Overview

Our WebSocket server provides real-time updates for events, notifications, and data changes.

## Connection

### Endpoint

```
wss://api.example.com/v3/ws
```

### Authentication

```javascript
const ws = new WebSocket('wss://api.example.com/v3/ws');

ws.onopen = () => {
  ws.send(JSON.stringify({
    type: 'auth',
    token: 'your_jwt_token'
  }));
};
```

## Subscribing to Events

```javascript
ws.send(JSON.stringify({
  type: 'subscribe',
  channels: ['user.notifications', 'orders.updates']
}));
```

## Message Format

### Server  Client

```json
{
  "type": "notification",
  "channel": "user.notifications",
  "data": {
    "id": "notif_123",
    "message": "Order shipped"
  },
  "timestamp": "2024-11-16T16:45:00Z"
}
```

## Heartbeat

Server sends ping every 30 seconds:

```json
{"type": "ping"}
```

Client must respond with pong:

```javascript
ws.onmessage = (event) => {
  const msg = JSON.parse(event.data);
  if (msg.type === 'ping') {
    ws.send(JSON.stringify({type: 'pong'}));
  }
};
```

## Error Handling

```javascript
ws.onerror = (error) => {
  console.error('WebSocket error:', error);
};

ws.onclose = (event) => {
  if (event.code !== 1000) {
    // Reconnect logic
    setTimeout(connect, 5000);
  }
};
```"}

